claims:
1. A method, comprising:
determining, by the system, a first model of a joint moment based on a sum of moments generated from stimulus pulses from each contact of a set of multiple electrode contacts;
determining, by the system, a second model of an overlap between pairs of contacts of the set of multiple electrode contacts;
determining, by the system, a stimulation parameter that maximizes the joint moment and minimizes the overlap based on a function of the first model and the second model; and
configuring, by the system, an electrical stimulus to be applied to a nerve by the set of multiple electrode contacts based on the stimulation parameter.
